
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `clear` baraye paak kardan safe terminal estefade mishavad. Yani hameye chizhayi ke ghablan neveshte shodeh ast, hazf mishavad va safe az aval shoru mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 Dastoor `clear` gozine khassi nadarad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ clear

    🔹 Paak kardan safe terminal.  Digar hich chizi az dastoorat ya khrooji-ha ghabli namayesh dade nemishavad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ clear
    
    🔹  Bad az ejraye in dastoor, safe terminal shoma kamelan khali mishavad va amade dastoore jadid mishavad.  Mesle inke yek safe jadid baz kardeid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `clear` command is used to clear the terminal screen. It removes all previous output and commands, providing a fresh, clean terminal.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 The `clear` command does not have any specific options.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ clear

    🔹 Clears the terminal screen. No previous commands or outputs will be visible.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ clear
    
    🔹 After executing this command, your terminal screen will be completely empty and ready for a new command. It's like opening a new terminal window.

